Joe Bundoc shared MarineBio.org's photo to the group: Filipino Freethinkers [Updates and Announcements].
2 hrs ·

[VERY SERIOUS]
*Sorry for the blatant use of profanities in this post. This is a very important issue for me. Thanks.

I am a self-proclaimed dumpling/siomai lover/connoisseur but I NEVER EVER order Shark's Fin siomai or dumpling or any food that includes the fin of a shark because of the wanton killings of sharks and their species. So please! Please! Never ever order any food that includes shark's fin.

...

The role that shark's play in the ocean is very vital and completely irreplaceable, as apex predators they regulate the population of prey fish such as tuna, anchovies, minnows and the like keeping the population healthy and keeping the balance of the ocean's ecosystem in check, here's a link to know more about the importance of sharks http://www.sharksavers.org/…/the-…/sharks-role-in-the-ocean/

Most shark species are critically endangered or close to being one because of over-hunting and fishing and of course habitat loss.

To those who would argue that its "masarap" kaya I'll keep ordering it nonetheless or "marami namang sharks sa ocean eh okay lang yan", get your heads out of your asses and go eat a dick, motherfuckers!

https://www.facebook.com/marinebio.org/photos/a.276954829060448.62830.120184188070847/497715706984358/?type=1&theater

See More
MarineBio.org

Someone confessed to us today that while dining out for dinner a few days ago in a restaurant in Richmond BC, Canada they enjoyed a bowl of shark fin soup - Inn...ocently and without knowing anything regarding how fins are obtained or the grave danger this very soup causes millions of sharks on our planet.
Thankfully a family member filled them in 2 days later and this individual was shocked to hear these animals are just dumped back into the Ocean to drown at the bottom mercilessly for overpriced soup... and only because they have fins.
This person had no idea about this practice and was horrified to know the truth...

We need to create more awareness.

Please pass this post along and if anyone knows the names of any of these restaurants serving shark fin soup... please (IM) or email us.

Thank you
MarineBio.org

www.jeffrotman.com
